.Dd February 20, 2026
.Dt FLUXSNAP 1
.Os
.Sh NAME
.Nm fluxsnap
.Nd keyboard-triggered smart tiling for Fluxbox/X11
.Sh SYNOPSIS
.Nm
.Op Fl c Ar config
.Sh DESCRIPTION
.Nm
listens for a configured hotkey (default: Super+Space).
When triggered, it tiles all normal windows across three columns with configured gaps.
.Pp
After tiling, clicking a window opens a small placement menu near the pointer with
"Left", "Middle", and "Right" choices.
The selected column preference is remembered for that window and reused in future tiling passes.
.Pp
Newly mapped windows are automatically tiled into the layout.
.Pp
The EWMH workarea is honored, so Fluxbox toolbar/slit/dock reserved space is respected.
.Sh OPTIONS
.Bl -tag -width indent
.It Fl c Ar config
Path to a configuration file.
.It Fl h
Show usage help.
.El
.Sh CONFIGURATION
Supported keys:
.Bl -tag -width hotkey
.It Ic modifier
Super, Mod4, Alt, Mod1, Ctrl, Control, or Shift.
.It Ic hotkey
X keysym string such as
.Dq space ,
.Dq F12 ,
or
.Dq Return .
.It Ic gap
Gap in pixels around and between tiled windows.
.El
.Sh FLUXBOX INTEGRATION
Run:
.Bd -literal -offset indent
fluxsnap-fluxbox-install
.Ed
.Pp
This helper merges snippets into:
.Bl -bullet -compact
.It
.Pa ~/.fluxbox/menu
.It
.Pa ~/.fluxbox/keys
.It
.Pa ~/.fluxbox/init
.El
and reloads Fluxbox.
.Sh INSTALLATION
.Bd -literal -offset indent
make
doas make install
.Ed
.Sh SEE ALSO
.Xr fluxbox 1
